{"word":"προσηνής","slug":"προσηνής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>προσηνής</b></el> <el>(προς-ηνής, <el>doric</el> <el>προς-ᾱνής</el>, and <el>ποτ-ᾱνής, ές</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>soft, gentle, kindly</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>; <el>προσηνές τι λέγειν</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <el>λύχνῳ προσηνές</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>suitable</i> for burning, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b> (For <a href='S:derived, derivation'>deriv.</a>, <a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:ἀπηνής'><el>ἀπηνής</el></a>). <p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-νῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Theophrastus'>Theophr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}